{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 19:38:03.566519", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nOverview\n- Observed a complete data-plane outage across the tenant subnet 10.0.0.0/24. All host-to-host communication (even intra-leaf) fails.\n- Management network 20.0.0.0/24 is healthy; all switches can reach the SDN controller IP (20.0.0.100) via ICMP.\n\nKey Findings (Evidence)\n1) End-host reachability\n- host_1_1 -> host_1_2 (same leaf) and cross-leaf pings all fail with “Destination Host Unreachable.”\n- ARP on host_1_1 shows incomplete entries for peers (e.g., 10.0.0.2, 10.0.0.5, 10.0.0.6, 10.0.0.9), indicating ARP requests are not being bridged/flooded.\n\n2) Switch control-plane state (OVS)\n- All switches (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1) are configured with Controller \"tcp:20.0.0.100:6633\" and fail_mode: secure.\n- Controller connection status on all switches: is_connected=false; status reports last_error=\"Connection timed out\", state CONNECTING/BACKOFF.\n- Flow tables are empty on all switches (ovs-ofctl dump-flows returns no entries).\n\n3) Management-plane connectivity\n- leaf_1 (20.0.0.3), leaf_2 (20.0.0.4), and spine_1 (20.0.0.1) can ping 20.0.0.100 successfully, confirming:\n  - Management interfaces are up and correctly addressed.\n  - IP reachability to the controller host is fine at layer 3.\n  - The timeouts correspond to TCP/6633 connection attempts, not to general IP reachability.\n\n4) Data-plane interfaces\n- All relevant OVS dataplane interfaces (eth0/1 to hosts, eth2/3 uplinks) are UP/LOWER_UP.\n- No local switching occurs because OVS is in secure fail mode with no flows and no controller.\n\nImpact\n- With fail_mode=secure and no connected controller, OVS drops all traffic, including ARP. This results in 100% host-to-host packet loss across the 10.0.0.0/24 subnet.\n\nFault Localization\n- Not a link or host NIC issue: interfaces are up and hosts are correctly addressed in 10.0.0.0/24.\n- Not a management network issue: switches reach 20.0.0.100 via ICMP.\n- Centralized at the SDN control-plane endpoint: tcp:20.0.0.100:6633 is not accepting OpenFlow connections from the switches.\n\nRoot Cause Assessment\n- The OpenFlow controller service at 20.0.0.100 on TCP port 6633 is unreachable from the switches at the TCP level (timeouts).\n- Likely causes include:\n  - Controller process not running, or listening on a different port (e.g., 6653 vs. 6633).\n  - Firewall/ACL blocking TCP/6633 on the controller host.\n- Because the controller is unreachable and OVS is in fail_mode=secure with no preinstalled flows, the switches drop all frames, causing system-wide ARP failure and complete tenant network outage.\n\nSummary\n- Anomaly detected: Yes — total tenant data-plane outage.\n- Faulty component: SDN controller endpoint/service at 20.0.0.100:6633 (control-plane).\n- Root cause: Controller not accepting TCP connections on the configured OpenFlow port, leading OVS (fail_mode=secure) to install no flows and drop all traffic.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 12965, "output_tokens": 2647, "total_tokens": 15612, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 10368}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 1856}}}
